5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT AUTHORIZING COUNTY COMMISSIONERS TO INITIATE
6 MANDAMUS PROCEEDINGS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 7-4-2110 AND 27-26-206, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 7-4-2110, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "7-4-2110. Supervision of county and other officers. (1) The board of county commissioners has
12 jurisdiction and power, under the limitations and restrictions that are prescribed by law, to:
13 (a) supervise the official conduct of all county officers and officers of all districts and other
14 subdivisions of the county charged with assessing, collecting, safekeeping, managing, or disbursing public
15 revenue;
16 (b) see that the officers faithfully perform their duties;
17 (c) direct prosecutions for delinquencies;
18 (d) when necessary, require the officers to renew their official bonds, make reports, and present
19 their books and accounts for inspection; and
20 (e) require the officers to supervise staff in a manner that complies with personnel policies and
21 procedures adopted by the county governing body. ;
22 (f) initiate civil proceedings to seek a writ of mandamus to compel or enjoin the performance of an
23 act by a local government entity within the county or any member of its governing body; and
24 (g) hire outside counsel to litigate a proceeding seeking a writ of mandamus and recover attorney
25 fees and costs as determined by a court.
26 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (2)(b), as used in this section, "local government entity"
27 has the meaning provided in 2-7-501.
28 (b) The term does not include a county, consolidated city-county, incorporated city or town, or
